  "prompt": "You are taking a TIER 5 technical evaluation for STANDARD models.\n\nSolve 5 JavaScript exercises inspired by a high school curriculum (1ère).\n\nReturn your answers in Markdown using headers for the exercise IDs and code blocks for the JavaScript functions.\n\n[EXERCISE Math]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"moyennePonderee(notes)\" that takes an array of {valeur, coeff} objects and returns the weighted average. Return 0 if array is empty.\n\n[EXERCISE Francais]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"frequenceMots(phrase)\" that returns an object with the count of each word in the string. Assume space separation.\n\n[EXERCISE SVT]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"transcrireADN(adn)\" that converts 'A'->'U', 'T'->'A', 'C'->'G', 'G'->'C' (ADN to ARN).\n\n[EXERCISE Histoire]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"grouperParEpoque(evenements)\" that takes an array of {nom, epoque} and returns an object grouping names by 'epoque'.\n\n[EXERCISE Info]\nWrite a JavaScript class \"FeuTricolore\" with a method \"passerAuSuivant()\" that cycles a 'couleur' property through 'rouge' -> 'vert' -> 'orange' -> 'rouge'. Constructor starts at 'rouge'.\n\nExpected strict response format:\n{\n  \"math\": \"function moyennePonderee(...) { ... }\",\n  \"francais\": \"function frequenceMots(...) { ... }\",\n  \"svt\": \"function transcrireADN(...) { ... }\",\n  \"histoire\": \"function grouperParEpoque(...) { ... }\",\n  \"info\": \"class FeuTricolore { ... }\"\n}",
